      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Let the user know that a team member from the clinic will give them a call back on the number they're calling from.\n\nSay something like:\n\"I'll make sure someone from the clinic gives you a call back on this number. They'll be able to help you with everything we discussed. Is this ok?\"\n\nIf the user asks when:\n\"Typically within the same business day, but it may be the \nnext business day if it's late in the afternoon or over the \nweekend.\"\n\nIf the user asks who will call:\n\"It'll be one of our front desk team members — they'll have \nthe notes from our conversation so you won't have to repeat \nanything.\"\n\nIf the user says that's NOT a good number:\n\"No problem — what's the best number to reach you?\" \nCollect the number, read it back, and confirm."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Exit Component",
